<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870626-0018 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Braniff Inc.</HL><DD> 06/26/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> BAIR </IN><TEXT>   BRANIFF INC., Dallas, is &quot;very optimistic&quot; about its second quarter ending July 31, J. Patrick Foley, chief executive officer, told the annual meeting. Following the meeting, he said he couldn't predict whether the airline would be profitable in the quarter, but he said that &quot;it will be very close. He said efforts to revamp marketing and cut fares have boosted load factors and increased advance bookings. Braniff is 69%-owned by Dalfort Corp., a Dallas aircraft-services and smokeless-tobacco concern that is closely held by the Pritzker family of Chicago. </TEXT></DOC>